This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method to improve the generalization performance of support vector machine under noisy environments. It also discusses the challenges of handling non-convexity induced by ramp loss in RSVM, which is a common problem in machine learning. Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in machine learning research. 

The paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. 

The paper discusses the application of RSVM to image classification problems, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper proposes a safe sample screening method, which involves selecting a subset of training samples to reduce computational time. This suggests that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves developing an algorithm to solve a computational problem. 

Finally, the paper proposes a concave-convex procedure (CCCP) framework to address the non-convexity problem in RSVM, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as CCCP is a common optimization technique used in neural networks.
